Text.Value: Do you think yourself wiser than Vlaakith herself?
No. Merely the most efficient.
That, or enslaved them. Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith. 'Vlaakith's will above all.'
Chk. Are you also sorry for the roaches you crush under your feet? For the weeds you pluck, and the vermin you slay?
The Dawnstar. A beacon to Lathander's faithful - and a startlingly potent artefact.

EditorData.logicalname: Knows about artefact already - Companion Gale

Text.Value: *A brilliant light shines from the temple's crest - a magical artefact of uncertain power.*
Not to mention a fine site for a crèche, concealed among the peaks and ridges.
Barbaric. Is violence your solution for everything?
As it must be. In a crèche, there is purpose. In a temple, only platitudes and unheard prayer.
This is a temple of Lathander. Or was, before the githyanki took over.
I fear this rock has twisted your mind more than the parasite ever could.
Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith. 'Vlaakith's will above all.'

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The cable car arrives, revealing a dead body on it.

Text.Value: A temple to a trivial god, nested among the peaks. Fine grounds for a crèche.
Certainly, once you evict the priests. Although I imagine the gith slaughtered them?
And what of Lathander's faithful? Did the githyanki cut them down?
The gith saw what they wanted and took it. Makes sense to me.
Well spoken, ra'stil.
It's gorgeous. We could use something like that.

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (Knows about artefact already - Companion Gale)

Text.Value: *Above the temple shines the most radiant of lights: the Dawnstar. A beacon to the god Lathander's faithful - and a startlingly potent weapon.*
And Lathander's priests? Did the githyanki just - kill them and take over?
Vlaakith sounds cruel and opportunistic, if you ask me.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The camera shows the Monastery (the Crèche) and the big shiny gem on the roof. You can hear the cable car traveling to you.

Text.Value: The original occupants might object - unless the gith just slaughtered them?
Keep silent.
